shared_text:
Nebraska State Education Association
July 15 at 11:34 AM ·

Nebraska has been approved for the Pandemic-EBT program! That means families that were on the Free or Reduced Price Lunch (FRPL) program for the 19-20 school year are eligible to receive the cost of meals missed because of COVID-19 school closures on an EBT card. Families eligible for FRPL for the full period of school closure will receive a total of $281 for the days closed per child. Deadline is July 19th! https://cip-dhhs.ne.gov/redcap/surveys/?s=DM3WNPMJN7

Nebraska State Education Association
July 15 at 11:34 AM ·

Nebraska has been approved for the Pandemic-EBT program! That means families that were on the Free or Reduced Price Lunch (FRPL) program for the 19-20 school year are eligible to receive the cost of meals missed because of COVID-19 school closures on an EBT card. Families eligible for FRPL for the full period of school closure will receive a total of $281 for the days closed per child. Deadline is July 19th! https://cip-dhhs.ne.gov/redcap/surveys/?s=DM3WNPMJN7

Elementary Home Room Teacher Update:

Typically home room teachers are available for students and families to see by July 15th. Due to summer school being moved to July this year, we currently have an "active school session" happening. This means, we can not activate the 2020-2021 school year until the completion of summer school. Families will now be able to view their child's homeroom teacher on August 1st, 2020. We apologize for the inconvenience and appreciate your patience and understanding!

post_text:
Hello Wildcat Families!

We have had some calls about the "fees" notifications that are being sent out to families.

Here is the process for fees: When a child is assessed a fee by a teacher or coach it is entered into Infinite Campus. Then you as a parent/guardian receive an email/call with the notification.

In order to see what the fee is, you will need to log into Infinite Campus, on the left side of the portal there is a button called "fees." Click on that button and you will see a list of fees assessed to your child...for details, click on the fee on the right side and it will give a description. If you have questions please email Mr. Kleinsasser: don.kleinsasser@spwildcat.org

To pay fees, please take the payment to the High School Office (Wardyn) or the Superintendent's office (Townsend). They will take your payment and remove the fee from Infinite Campus; all fees need to be paid by the end of the school year.

Thank you
St. Paul Public Schools

St. Paul Library
April 9 at 4:11 PM ·

The St. Paul Library closed the drop box this week due to directives we were given not to take items back from the public until the COVID-19 activity in our area decreases. There are no staff members in the building- we are remotely working from home as needed.

❌❌That being said, please do NOT place books outside our building in hopes we will check them in.❌❌

You are not being charged late fees during this time. So please, just hold on to them until we are able to process returns. When you check a book out from the library, it’s your responsibility to keep the book from getting damaged. By placing the books outside you are susceptible to book theft and book damage which will be the patrons responsibility to replace.

Please stay home everyone. Please stay safe.

shared_text:
St. Paul Civic Center
March 30 at 3:23 PM ·

THE COMMUNITY WORD HUNT!!
PLEASE SHARE!!!!

Residents & BUSINESSES- Please use a sheet of paper and a marker and post a word in your window! The word must start with the same letter as your street name! (Tenth Street Would be T) Try to be creative and a little silly with your word! 😁🙃

Kids- You must go around and find as many words as you can!! Once you find your words take them home and put them into a paragraph using as many words as you can!! The St. Paul Civic Center would love to see your paragraphs! You can post them on our Facebook page! You can use the following words for FREE words as many times as you want.
THE, UP, BLUE, AND, IS, ARE, HE, SHE, THEY, IT, BALD, HUGE, KIND, CALM, CAREFULLY, VERY, OUT, I, NEVER AND TODAY!!

Post your words on your windows today 3/30! COMMUNITY WORD HUNT starts TOMORROW and will go until Friday!! PLEASE SHARE!

It is a recommendation that students spend at least 2 hours engaged in intentional learning, which includes reading, accessing on-line resources, puzzles etc. There are hard copy packets for students who don't have access to internet or a device available in the elementary office. We are currently having discussions about elementary students being allowed to check-out chrome books. More information will be available later next week. Hard copy packets can be picked up in the elementary office today until 4:00 p.m. and during the week Monday-Thursday 8:00-12:00 or you can call the elementary office and make an appointment! 7-12 St. Paul Public School Parent/Student Announcements (3-18-20):

Jr/Sr. High families without internet access or, without unlimited data on your cellular phones, please call Mrs. Wardyn so that we can make a list of students without access (308) 754-4433.

Students that forgot to pick up their books when they left school on March 16, 2020:
You may come to Mrs. Wardyn’s office:
Thursday, March 19th, from 8-4 p.m.;
Friday, March 20th, from 8-4 p.m.; or
Saturday, March 21st from 9 - 10:30 a.m.

post_text:
Sponsored by: Hall County Community Collaborative (H3C)

All parents wonder if they’re getting it right. You’re not alone. Sometimes it’s hard to tell what your child needs, what her behaviors mean and if you’re doing right by him. Imagine what it might feel like if you could make sense of what your child is really asking from you.

Circle of Security™ Parenting is an opportunity to join other parents just like you, for an 8-week class where you’ll learn to:

• Strengthen your relationship with your child

• Be present with your child during the best and toughest of times

• Recognize your child’s needs and make sense of his or her behavior

Who should attend: Anyone who cares about kids!

Location: Head Start, 310 N Piper Street, Grand Island

Dates/Times: Thursdays, Beginning January 16th through March 5th from 5:30 – 7:30pm

Cost: FREE

How to register: Visit calendar at www.necosp.org or Email Ssmith@gips.org

Class Instructor: Sally Smith, LCSW

Sponsored by: Hall County Community Collaborative (H3C)

St. Paul Public Schools would like to inform you of some schedule changes for the current week.

There will be a pep rally for the volleyball team Wednesday November 6th at 3:00 pm in the HS Gym.

Due to the Volleyball team qualifying for the state tournament, there will be no school on Thursday November 7th. The Volleyball team will be playing their first game at 1:30 pm on Thursday at the Lincoln North Star High School.

There is also no school on Friday November 8th due to fall break.

On Friday November 8th, the football team will be playing Aquinas Catholic. The game will be in St. Paul and will start at 7:00 pm Friday night.

On Monday November 11th there will be a veterans day program in the HS Gym starting at 10:00 am.

Thank you and Good Luck Wildcats.
